'''Neo Booker T Washingtonism''' is a continued [[Conceptualisation|conceptualization]] of [[Booker T. Washington|Booker T Washington's]] position in the 1960s [[civil rights movement]] of assuaging [[race relations]] between white and black Americans by positing that blacks should postpone their aspirations of full [[civil rights]] and work within the system of the [[government]] to ultimately be accepted in the long run as productive citizens.

